list.abstract: park（英 [pɑːk]，美 [pɑːrk]），英语单词，作名词为公园；庭园；专用场地；停车制动挡。作动词为停放；把…停在路边；把…开进停车场。例句：I think you can park there.（我想你可以在那里停车。） 近义词有stopping place。

yingyinNormal.en: Today, Peppa is going to the park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天佩佩打算去公园。

yingyinNormal.en: And the next stop, St James' Park Station.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下一站，圣詹姆斯公园。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the park. We're here! Hooray!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是公园。我们到了！太棒了！

yingyinNormal.en: Central Park? Yeah. All of us. All day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中央公园？对，大家一起，去个一整天。

yingyinNormal.en: And the car is empty at St James's Park Station.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到了圣詹姆斯公园，车就空了。

yingyinNormal.en: Closer to town is Singapore's big backyard, East Coast Park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而较接近市中心的是新加坡最大的后花园——东海岸公园。

yingyinNormal.en: She did a number on a public park. A park on my beat. My park. I watch that park every day. I'm sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她对公园大动了一番手脚，我管辖的公园，我的公园，我每天都要去那个公园。我很抱歉。

yingyinNormal.en: And the park for one hour every other Sunday for fresh air.
yingyinNormal.zh: 隔周周日送我去公园呼吸新鲜空气。

yingyinNormal.en: Green Park and St. James's Park are right next to Buckingham Palace, Admiralty Arch and The Mall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 绿园和圣詹姆斯公园就在白金汉宫、海军拱门和林荫路的旁边。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, we thought we would all go to a picnic in Central Park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以一起去野餐，就去中央公园。

yingyinNormal.en: That sucks. That's not a trip. I just came from the park.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么鸟地方？那根本不算旅行，我才刚从公园过来。

yingyinNormal.en: Think of cleaning up this park as an opportunity. To get hepatitis?
yingyinNormal.zh: 把清洁这座公园当成一个机会。得肝炎的机会吗？

yingyinNormal.en: What guy? The guy. He was at the park. He said it was a time machine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哪个家伙? 在公园里的那人，他说这是时光机。

yingyinNormal.en: Days later, you're walking in the park when suddenly it starts to pour rain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几天之后，你在公园散步突然下了一场大雨。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, where is everybody? They took Ben to the park. Where have you been?
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家到哪里去了？ 带班去公园了，你去哪里了？

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, I don't want to like scare kids at the park, or anything like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可不想成为整天在公园里吓唬小孩的那种人。

yingyinNormal.en: Do I go horseback riding in the park? Do I take classes at the New School? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我到过公园骑马吗？我在新学校上过课吗？没有。

yingyinNormal.en: Today, Peppa is going to the park. It's freezing cold. It is cold.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天，佩奇一家人要去公园。我觉得今天好冷啊。确实是很冷。

yingyinNormal.en: This beach park is part of Kailua-Kona, the island's main resort hub.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个海滩公园是凯鲁瓦科纳的一部份，岛上的主要度假胜地。

yingyinNormal.en: It vanishes between St James's Park and Westminster. Lord Moran vanishes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它在圣詹姆斯公园和西敏寺站台间消失，莫兰爵士也消失了。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Every Saturday morning, at 9 am, more than 50, 000 runners set off to run 5km around their local <highlight>park</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周六上午9点，超过50000名跑步者出发绕着他们当地的公园跑5公里。

examination_example.sentence: Hill's pressure later led to the creation of national <highlight>parks</highlight> and green belts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 希尔的压力后来促成了国家公园和绿化带的建立。

examination_example.sentence: Parks feature, particularly in the earlier works, such as John Hilliard's very funny Across the <highlight>Park</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尤其在早期的作品中，约翰·希利亚德《穿越公园》的公园特色明显。

examination_example.sentence: Julie <highlight>Parks</highlight> of Grand Rapids Community College points to another key to luring Millennials into manufacturing: a work/life balance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大急流社区学院的Julie Parks指出了吸引千禧一代进入制造业的另一个关键：工作与生活的平衡。

examination_example.sentence: The modern mind, Tim <highlight>Parks</highlight>, a novelist and critic, writes, "is overwhelmingly inclined toward communication."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 小说家兼评论家Tim Parks写道，现代人的思维“绝大多数倾向于交流”。

examination_example.sentence: Some rest in the shade of a <highlight>parked</highlight> car.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其中一些在汽车的荫蔽中休息。

word_usage.usage:
park表“公园”时，为可数名词，其前的介词习惯用in。注意park用于表示公园名称时，其前无论是专有名词还是普通名词，习惯上都不加the。
示例：北海公园非常美丽。
误 The Beihai Park is very beautiful.
正 Beihai Park is very beautiful.
